  "question": "Amortized Analysis",
  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n<title>Amortized Analysis — Interactive Demo</title>\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\" />\n<style>\n  body { font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", Roboto, \"Helvetica Neue\", Arial; margin: 20px; color:#111; background: #f6f8fb; }\n  h1 { margin: 0 0 8px; font-size: 22px; }\n  p.lead { margin: 4px 0 14px; color:#333; }\n  .container { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 360px 1fr; gap: 18px; align-items: start; }\n  .panel { background: #fff; padding: 14px; border-radius: 8px; box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(27,31,35,0.06); }\n  label { display:block; margin-top: 8px; font-weight:600; font-size:13px; }\n  .controls { display:flex; gap:8px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin-top:8px; }\n  button { padding:8px 10px; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid #c7cfe0; background:#f7fbff; cursor:pointer; }\n  button.primary { background:#1f7aed; color:white; border-color:#1660d6; }\n  button:active { transform: translateY(1px); }\n  input[type=number], select { padding:6px 8px; border-radius:6px; border:1px solid #d6dce8; }\n  .small { font-size:13px; color:#555; margin-top:8px; }\n  canvas { width:100%; height:260px; background: linear-gradient(#fff,#fbfdff); border-radius:6px; box-shadow: inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.6); }\n  .stats { display:flex; gap:10px; margin-top:10px; flex-wrap:wrap; }\n  .stat { background:#f3f7ff; padding:8px 10px; border-radius:6px; font-weight:600; color:#10307a; }\n  .explain { margin-top:12px; font-size:14px; line-height:1.5; color:#222; }\n  .explain .muted { color:#555; font-weight:600; margin-top:8px; display:block; }\n  footer { margin-top:16px; font-size:12px; color:#444; }\n  .legend { display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center; margin-top:8px; font-size:13px; }\n  .swatch { width:12px; height:12px; border-radius:2px; display:inline-block; }\n  .controls-row { display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center; margin-top:8px; }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <h1>Amortized Analysis — Interactive Demos</h1>\n  <p class=\"lead\">See how average (amortized) cost per operation differs from the worst-case cost by simulating common examples: dynamic array (doubling) and binary counter.</p>\n\n  <div class=\"container\">\n    <div class=\"panel\" style=\"position:sticky; top:20px;\">\n      <label>Choose demo</label>\n      <select id=\"demoSelect\">\n        <option value=\"dynamic\">Dynamic array (doubling resize)</option>\n        <option value=\"binary\">Binary counter (increment flips)</option>\n      </select>\n\n      <div id=\"dynamicControls\">\n        <label>Starting capacity</label>\n        <input id=\"startCapacity\" type=\"number\" min=\"1\" value=\"1\" />\n        <label>Resize strategy</label>\n        <select id=\"resizeStrategy\">\n          <option value=\"double\">Double capacity (×2)</option>\n          <option value=\"increment\">Grow by 1 (bad strategy)</option>\n          <option value=\"factor1.5\">Grow by 1.5 (approx)</option>\n        </select>\n        <label>Number of push operations to simulate</label>\n        <input id=\"opsCount\" type=\"number\" min=\"1\" value=\"100\" />\n      </div>\n\n      <div id=\"binaryControls\" style=\"display:none;\">\n        <label>Number of bits in counter</label>\n        <input id=\"bits\" type=\"number\" min=\"1\" value=\"10\" />\n        <label>Number of increment operations to simulate</label>\n        <input id=\"opsCountBinary\" type=\"number\" min=\"1\" value=\"100\" />\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"controls\">\n        <button id=\"stepBtn\">Step</button>\n        <button id=\"runBtn\" class=\"primary\">Run</button>\n        <button id=\"fastRunBtn\">Fast Run</button>\n        <button id=\"resetBtn\">Reset</button>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"controls-row\">\n        <label style=\"margin:0;\">Speed</label>\n        <input id=\"delay\" type=\"number\" min=\"0\" value=\"60\" style=\"width:80px\" /> ms per step\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"small\">Tips: Use \"double\" growth to see amortized O(1) push. Use \"increment\" to see O(n) amortized push (average ≈ O(n)). Binary counter shows amortized cost O(1) because most increments flip few bits.</div>\n\n      <div class=\"stats\" id=\"statRow\" >\n        <div class=\"stat\" id=\"totalCost\">Total: 0</div>\n        <div class=\"stat\" id=\"lastCost\">Last: 0</div>\n        <div class=\"stat\" id=\"avgCost\">Amortized: 0.00</div>\n        <div class=\"stat\" id=\"opCount\">Ops: 0</div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"legend\">\n        <div><span class=\"swatch\" style=\"background:#2479ff\"></span> per-op cost</div>\n        <div><span class=\"swatch\" style=\"background:#27c281\"></span> running average</div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"explain\">\n        <span class=\"muted\">What's happening?</span>\n        <div id=\"explainText\">Select a demo and run operations. Watch the cost each operation (bars) and the running average (green line). In amortized analysis we ask: over a sequence of operations, what is the average cost per operation in the worst case?</div>\n      </div>\n\n      <footer>\n        Amortized techniques: aggregate, accounting, potential. Examples here visualize aggregate (total cost / #ops) and show why doubling gives amortized O(1).\n      </footer>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"panel\">\n      <canvas id=\"chart\" width=\"800\" height=\"260\"></canvas>\n      <div style=\"margin-top:10px; font-size:13px; color:#444;\">\n        Chart: blue bars = cost of each operation (vertical). Green line = running average (amortized cost).\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n<script>\n(() => {\n  // Utilities\n  const $ = id => document.getElementById(id);\n  const chart = $('chart');\n  const ctx = chart.getContext('2d');\n\n  // State\n  let demo = 'dynamic';\n  let running = false;\n  let timer = null;\n  let stepDelay = 60;\n  let maxBars = 400;\n\n  // Simulation data arrays\n  let costs = [];   // per-op costs\n  let avg = [];     // running average after each op\n  let opIndex = 0;\n\n  // Dynamic array state\n  let size = 0, capacity = 1;\n  let strategy = 'double';\n  let startCap = 1;\n  let opsToDo = 100;\n\n  // Binary counter state\n  let bits = 10;\n  let counter = []; // array of 0/1\n  let opsBinary = 100;\n\n  // DOM elements\n  const demoSelect = $('demoSelect');\n  const startCapacity = $('startCapacity');\n  const resizeStrategy = $('resizeStrategy');\n  const opsCount = $('opsCount');\n  const bitsInput = $('bits');\n  const opsCountBinary = $('opsCountBinary');\n  const stepBtn = $('stepBtn');\n  const runBtn = $('runBtn');\n  const fastRunBtn = $('fastRunBtn');\n  const resetBtn = $('resetBtn');\n  const delayInput = $('delay');\n  const totalCostEl = $('totalCost');\n  const lastCostEl = $('lastCost');\n  const avgCostEl = $('avgCost');\n  const opCountEl = $('opCount');\n  const explainText = $('explainText');\n  const dynamicControls = $('dynamicControls');\n  const binaryControls = $('binaryControls');\n\n  // Canvas drawing helpers\n  function clearCanvas() {\n    ctx.clearRect(0,0,chart.width, chart.height);\n  }\n  function draw() {\n    clearCanvas();\n    const w = chart.width;\n    const h = chart.height;\n    const n = costs.length;\n    if (n === 0) return;\n\n    // compute scale\n    const maxCost = Math.max(1, Math.max(...costs));\n    // We'll ensure bars fit horizontally: show last up to maxBars\n    const showStart = Math.max(0, n - maxBars);\n    const shown = costs.slice(showStart);\n    const shownAvg = avg.slice(showStart);\n    const bw = Math.max(2, Math.floor(w / Math.max(1, shown.length)));\n    // draw bars\n    for (let i = 0; i < shown.length; i++) {\n      const c = shown[i];\n      const x = i * bw;\n      const barH = Math.round((c / maxCost) * (h - 30));\n      ctx.fillStyle = '#2479ff';\n      ctx.fillRect(x + 1, h - barH - 20, bw - 2, barH);\n    }\n    // draw average curve (green) smoothed\n    ctx.beginPath();\n    ctx.lineWidth = 2;\n    ctx.strokeStyle = '#27c281';\n    for (let i = 0; i < shownAvg.length; i++) {\n      const a = shownAvg[i];\n      const x = i * bw + (bw / 2);\n      const y = h - (a / maxCost) * (h - 30) - 20;\n      if (i === 0) ctx.moveTo(x,y); else ctx.lineTo(x,y);\n    }\n    ctx.stroke();\n\n    // axes labels: right side show maxCost\n    ctx.fillStyle = '#333';\n    ctx.font = '12px system-ui, Arial';\n    ctx.fillText('max cost ≈ ' + maxCost, 6, 14);\n    ctx.fillText('ops shown: ' + shown.length, 6, 28);\n  }\n\n  // Simulation functions\n  function resetSimulation() {\n    costs = [];\n    avg = [];\n    opIndex = 0;\n    running = false;\n    clearTimeout(timer);\n    timer = null;\n    // pick demo values from inputs\n    demo = demoSelect.value;\n    stepDelay = Number(delayInput.value) || 0;\n\n    if (demo === 'dynamic') {\n      dynamicControls.style.display = '';\n      binaryControls.style.display = 'none';\n      size = 0;\n      startCap = Math.max(1, parseInt(startCapacity.value,10) || 1);\n      capacity = startCap;\n      strategy = resizeStrategy.value;\n      opsToDo = Math.max(1, parseInt(opsCount.value,10) || 1);\n      explainText.innerHTML = 'Dynamic array: each push costs 1 normally. When the array is full it must be resized: allocate new array and copy all elements (cost proportional to capacity). Doubling (×2) gives amortized O(1) pushes; growing by 1 gives amortized O(n) pushes.';\n    } else {\n      dynamicControls.style.display = 'none';\n      binaryControls.style.display = '';\n      bits = Math.max(1, parseInt(bitsInput.value,10) || 1);\n      counter = new Array(bits).fill(0);\n      opsBinary = Math.max(1, parseInt(opsCountBinary.value,10) || 1);\n      explainText.innerHTML = 'Binary counter: increment flips trailing 1s to 0s and the first 0 to 1. The cost is number of bit flips. Over many increments the amortized number of bit flips per increment is O(1).';\n    }\n\n    updateStats();\n    draw();\n  }\n\n  function updateStats() {\n    const total = costs.reduce((a,b)=>a+b,0);\n    const last = costs.length ? costs[costs.length-1] : 0;\n    const amort = costs.length ? (total / costs.length) : 0;\n    totalCostEl.textContent = 'Total: ' + total;\n    lastCostEl.textContent = 'Last: ' + last;\n    avgCostEl.textContent = 'Amortized: ' + amort.toFixed(2);\n    opCountEl.textContent = 'Ops: ' + costs.length;\n  }\n\n  function stepOnce() {\n    if (demo === 'dynamic') {\n      // push operation\n      let cost = 1; // base cost to insert\n      if (size >= capacity) {\n        // resize cost: we copy 'capacity' items\n        cost += capacity;\n        // apply growth strategy\n        if (strategy === 'double') {\n          capacity = Math.max(1, capacity * 2);\n        } else if (strategy === 'increment') {\n          capacity = capacity + 1;\n        } else if (strategy === 'factor1.5') {\n          capacity = Math.floor(capacity * 1.5) + 1;\n        } else {\n          capacity = capacity * 2;\n        }\n      }\n      size++;\n      costs.push(cost);\n    } else {\n      // binary increment\n      let cost = 0;\n      for (let i = 0; i < counter.length; i++) {\n        cost++;\n        if (counter[i] === 0) {\n          counter[i] = 1;\n          break;\n        } else {\n          counter[i] = 0;\n        }\n        // if we flipped all bits and they were all 1, we've wrapped around\n      }\n      costs.push(cost);\n    }\n    // update running average\n    const total = costs.reduce((a,b)=>a+b,0);\n    avg.push(total / costs.length);\n    opIndex++;\n    updateStats();\n    draw();\n  }\n\n  function runSteps(n, fast=false) {\n    if (running) return;\n    running = true;\n    let remaining = n;\n    function loop() {\n      if (!running) return;\n      if (remaining <= 0) {\n        running = false;\n        return;\n      }\n      // do one step\n      stepOnce();\n      remaining--;\n      if (fast) {\n        // do batch quickly to avoid UI thrashing\n        // run many steps per animation frame if possible\n        const batch = Math.min(1000, remaining);\n        for (let b = 0; b < batch; b++) {\n          stepOnce();\n        }\n        remaining -= batch;\n        setTimeout(loop, 0);\n      } else {\n        timer = setTimeout(loop, stepDelay);\n      }\n    }\n    loop();\n  }\n\n  // Button actions\n  stepBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    runSteps(1);\n  });\n  runBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    // run requested number for current demo\n    if (demoSelect.value === 'dynamic') {\n      runSteps( Math.max(1, parseInt(opsCount.value,10) || 1) );\n    } else {\n      runSteps( Math.max(1, parseInt(opsCountBinary.value,10) || 1) );\n    }\n  });\n  fastRunBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    if (demoSelect.value === 'dynamic') {\n      runSteps( Math.max(1, parseInt(opsCount.value,10) || 1), true );\n    } else {\n      runSteps( Math.max(1, parseInt(opsCountBinary.value,10) || 1), true );\n    }\n  });\n  resetBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {\n    resetSimulation();\n  });\n\n  demoSelect.addEventListener('change', () => {\n    resetSimulation();\n  });\n  resizeStrategy.addEventListener('change', () => resetSimulation());\n  startCapacity.addEventListener('change', () => resetSimulation());\n  opsCount.addEventListener('change', () => {});\n  bitsInput.addEventListener('change', () => resetSimulation());\n  opsCountBinary.addEventListener('change', () => {});\n  delayInput.addEventListener('change', () => {\n    stepDelay = Number(delayInput.value) || 0;\n  });\n\n  // initial setup\n  resetSimulation();\n\n  // Extra: show explanatory examples when double strategy selected display theoretical amortized cost\n  resizeStrategy.addEventListener('change', () => {\n    const s = resizeStrategy.value;\n    if (s === 'double') {\n      explainText.innerHTML = 'Dynamic array (doubling): Even though some pushes cost O(n) when resizing, the total cost of n pushes is O(n). So amortized cost per push is O(1). Intuition: each element gets copied only O(1) times across all resizes.';\n    } else if (s === 'increment') {\n      explainText.innerHTML = 'Grow-by-1 strategy: Every push when full will copy all existing elements, so performing n pushes can cost O(n^2) in total; amortized cost per push is O(n). This is why growth factor matters.';\n    } else {\n      explainText.innerHTML = 'Sub-linear growth (e.g. ×1.5) still gives amortized O(1) pushes (though with different constants).';\n    }\n    resetSimulation();\n  });\n\n  // Resize canvas for high DPI\n  function resizeCanvas() {\n    const dpr = window.devicePixelRatio || 1;\n    chart.width = chart.clientWidth * dpr;\n    chart.height = chart.clientHeight * dpr;\n    ctx.scale(dpr, dpr);\n    draw();\n  }\n  window.addEventListener('resize', () => {\n    // reset transform then rescale\n    ctx.setTransform(1,0,0,1,0,0);\n    resizeCanvas();\n  });\n  resizeCanvas();\n\n  // Educational overlay: show aggregated theoretical info when enough ops run\n  setInterval(() => {\n    if (costs.length > 0 && demoSelect.value === 'dynamic' && resizeStrategy.value === 'double') {\n      // approximate theoretical amortized <= 3 (for doubling with cost model base=1 + copy)\n      const amort = costs.reduce((a,b)=>a+b,0)/costs.length;\n      if (amort < 3.5) {\n        explainText.innerHTML = 'Observation: The running average stabilizes near a small constant (≈2-3) — this is the amortized O(1) cost per push for doubling arrays under this simple cost model.';\n      }\n    }\n  }, 1000);\n})();\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
